-- CTC Media’s 4 Years-Plus Moscow Audience Rises, TNS Global Says
-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 2012-05-30T19:01:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/ctc-media-s-4-years-plus-moscow-audience-rises-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM)  average daily share of
viewers four-years-old and over in Moscow rose in the week to
May 27, data compiled by TNS-Global show.  The average daily audience among viewers four-years-old and
over in Moscow for CTC, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, rose to 6.6 percent in the
week to May 27 from 6.4 percent in the previous week, data
researcher TNS-Global said in an e-mail today.  CTC was the fifth-most-watched in audience rankings in the
category, the data show. NTV Television, Rossiya-1, Pervyi Kanal
and TNT ranked ahead of CTC, TNS-Global said. CTC outpaced REN
TV among viewers four-year-old and over.  The share of viewers aged 18 and older in Moscow for CTC
held at 5.8 percent for the week to May 27, TNS-Global data
show. NTV Television, Rossiya-1, Pervyi Kanal, and TNT ranked
ahead of CTC among Moscow viewers. REN TV gained to share the
fifth rank with CTC.  To contact the reporter on this story:
